class TweetCounts {
    private Map<String, List<Integer>> tweetTimes;

    public TweetCounts() {
        tweetTimes = new HashMap<>();
    }

    public void recordTweet(String tweetName, int time) {
        tweetTimes.computeIfAbsent(tweetName, k -> new ArrayList<>()).add(time);
    }

    public List<Integer> getTweetCountsPerFrequency(String freq, String tweetName, int startTime, int endTime) {
        List<Integer> times = tweetTimes.getOrDefault(tweetName, new ArrayList<>());
        int chunkSize = getChunkSize(freq);
        List<Integer> result = new ArrayList<>();

        for (int i = startTime; i <= endTime; i += chunkSize) {
            int count = 0;
            int endChunk = Math.min(i + chunkSize - 1, endTime);
            for (int time : times) {
                if (time >= i && time <= endChunk) {
                    count++;
                }
            }
            result.add(count);
        }
        return result;
    }

    private int getChunkSize(String freq) {
        switch (freq) {
            case "minute":
                return 60;
            case "hour":
                return 3600;
            case "day":
                return 86400;
            default:
                return 0;
        }
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n log n + m) for recordTweet and getTweetCountsPerFrequency respectively, where n is the number of tweets and m is the number of chunks.
time complexity (alternative): For recordTweet: O(1) amortized; For getTweetCountsPerFrequency: O(m*n) where m is the number of chunks and n is the number of tweets for a given tweetName.
space complexity: O(n) where n is the total number of tweets across all tweetNames.
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The main approach is to store the tweet times in a HashMap where the key is the tweetName and the value is a list of times when the tweet was recorded. When getting the tweet counts per frequency, we iterate over the time chunks and count the number of tweets that fall within each chunk. The key strengths are efficient storage and retrieval of tweet times, and the ability to handle different frequencies. The main weakness is the potential for slow performance when there are many tweets for a given tweetName and a large number of chunks.
